[src:automl/automated-machine-learning] AutoML potentially includes every stage from beginning with a raw dataset to building a machine learning model ready for deployment.
[src:automl/automated-machine-learning] AutoML was proposed as an artificial intelligence-based solution to the growing challenge of applying machine learning.
[src:automl/automated-machine-learning] The high degree of automation in AutoML aims to allow non-experts to make use of machine learning models and techniques without requiring them to become experts in machine learning.
[src:automl/automated-machine-learning] Automating the process of applying machine learning end-to-end additionally offers the advantages of producing simpler solutions, faster creation of those solutions, and models that often outperform hand-designed models.
[src:automl/automated-machine-learning] Common techniques used in AutoML include hyperparameter optimization, meta-learning and neural architecture search.
[src:automl/automated-machine-learning] In a typical machine learning application, practitioners have a set of input data points to be used for training.
[src:automl/automated-machine-learning] The raw data may not be in a form that all algorithms can be applied to.
[src:automl/automated-machine-learning] To make the data amenable for machine learning, an expert may have to apply appropriate data pre-processing, feature engineering, feature extraction, and feature selection methods.
[src:automl/automated-machine-learning] After these steps, practitioners must then perform algorithm selection and hyperparameter optimization to maximize the predictive performance of their model.
[src:automl/automated-machine-learning] If deep learning is used, the architecture of the neural network must also be chosen manually by the machine learning expert.
[src:automl/automated-machine-learning] Each of these steps may be challenging, resulting in significant hurdles to using machine learning.
[src:automl/automated-machine-learning] AutoML aims to simplify these steps for non-experts, and to make it easier for them to use machine learning techniques correctly and effectively.
[src:automl/automated-machine-learning] AutoML plays an important role within the broader approach of automating data science, which also includes challenging tasks such as data engineering, data exploration and model interpretation and prediction.
[src:automl/automated-machine-learning] Automated machine learning can target various stages of the machine learning process.
[src:automl/automated-machine-learning] There are a number of key challenges being tackled around automated machine learning.
[src:automl/automated-machine-learning] A big issue surrounding the field is referred to as "development as a cottage industry".
[src:automl/automated-machine-learning] This phrase refers to the issue in machine learning where development relies on manual decisions and biases of experts.
[src:automl/automated-machine-learning] This is contrasted to the goal of machine learning which is to create systems that can learn and improve from their own usage and analysis of the data.
[src:automl/automated-machine-learning] Basically, it's the struggle between how much experts should get involved in the learning of the systems versus how much freedom they should be giving the machines.
[src:automl/automated-machine-learning] However, experts and developers must help create and guide these machines to prepare them for their own learning.
[src:automl/automated-machine-learning] To create this system, it requires labor intensive work with knowledge of machine learning algorithms and system design.
[src:automl/automated-machine-learning] Additionally, other challenges include meta-learning and computational resource allocation.
[src:automl/bayesian-optimization] The method constructs a probabilistic model of the unknown function, often a Gaussian process (GP), and uses the resulting predictive distribution to choose the next evaluation point.
[src:automl/bayesian-optimization] This choice is made by optimizing a sampling criterion, also called an acquisition function.
[src:automl/bayesian-optimization] Common applications include hyperparameter optimization in machine learning, where each trial may require training and validating a model, and engineering design problems driven by expensive numerical simulations.
